{
  "texts": [
    "A wealth of software packages have been developed for portfolio optimization, many (if not most) with Python interfaces, both open-source and commercial.",
    "Examples range from simple web-based visualization tools to complex trading platforms.",
    "Here we mention only a few of these software implementations.",
    "On the simpler end Portfolio Visualizer [Glo23] is a web-based tool that allows users to back-test and visualize various portfolio strategies.",
    "PyPortfolioOpt [Mar21] and Cvxportfolio [BBD + 17] are Python packages offering various portfolio optimization techniques."
  ]
}